Headlines.Headline: NCR's 3Q Net Down After Teradata Spinoff

PARAGRAPH.#text: DAYTON, Ohio (AP)--NCR Corp. (NCR), which makes automated teller machines, said Wednesday that its third-quarter earnings fell 63%, reflecting the spinoff of Teradata Corp. (TDC). But the results beat Wall Street estimates, and NCR's stock jumped more than 9%.

Headlines.Headline: Teradata's 3Q Net Down On Spinoff Expenses

PARAGRAPH.#text: DAYTON, Ohio (AP)--Computer maker Teradata Corp. (TDC), in its first earnings report as a standalone company, said Tuesday its earnings fell 79% in the third quarter, in part because of expenses related to its spinoff from NCR Corp. (NCR).

Headlines.Author: Adam Edelman
Headlines.Headline: Teradata Corp 3Q EPS 5c Vs EPS 24c

#text: DOW JONES NEWSWIRES Teradata Corp.'s

third-quarter net income fell 80% to $9 million, or 5 cents a share, from $43 million, or 24 cents a share, a year earlier. Results for the latest period included 7 cents a share in expenses related to the company's spin off from NCR Corp., 11 cents a share related to an uncertain tax position and 6 cents a share related to a tax change in Germany.

Headlines.Headline: Teradata Enters $300M Credit Pact

#text: DOW JONES NEWSWIRES Teradata Corp.
said in a Tuesday Securities and Exchange Commission filing that it entered a $300 million five-year, unsecured credit agreement with a group of lenders. As reported, NCR Corp.
completed its spinoff of Teradata on Monday. Shares of Dayton, Ohio-based Teradata traded Wednesday afternoon at $26.42 each.

Headlines.Headline: Nasdaq Jumps 1.5% as Blue Chips Rally

PARAGRAPH.#text: The Nasdaq surged 1.5% Monday, its highest close in more than six years, as tech blue chips marched ahead. Acxiom plunged after buyout talks fell through, while Garmin shares tumbled after Nokia agreed to buy Navteq.
